        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1974-06-27T14:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1974-06-27T14:20:00-05:00" n="191"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <head>191. Memorandum of Conversation, Washington, June 27, 1974, 1520–1530.<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d191fn1">Source: Washington National Records
                        Center, <gloss target="#t_oasd-isa">OASD/ISA</gloss> Files: <gloss
                            target="#t_frc">FRC</gloss> 330–77–0054, Japan, 333, July 5, 1974.
                        Confidential. Prepared by Barrett and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Ellsworth</persName>. The conversation
                        took place in <persName corresp="#p_schlesinger-james-r"
                            >Schlesinger</persName>’s office. <persName
                            corresp="#p_schlesinger-james-r">Schlesinger</persName>’s talking
                        points, dated June 26, are ibid.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d191fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_hodgson-james-d">Hodgson</persName> and <persName
                            corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Ellsworth</persName> discussed military
                        issues involving the United States and Japan. <persName
                            corresp="#p_schlesinger-james-r">Schlesinger</persName> joined the
                        meeting for the last ten minutes.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1974-06-27T15:20:00-04:00" to="1974-06-27T15:30:00-04:00"
                            type="conversation-or-meeting-date">June 27, 1974, 1520–1530</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>ASSISTANT SECRETARY OF DEFENSE<lb/>WASHINGTON, D.C. 20301</p>
                <p>In reply refer to: 1-5940/74</p>
                <p>MEMORANDUM OF CONVERSATION</p>
                <p>SUBJECT: Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_hodgson-james-d">Hodgson</persName>’s
                    Courtesy Call with the Secretary of Defense</p>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS:</head>
                    <item>State Department</item>
                    <item>Ambassador to Japan - <persName corresp="#p_hodgson-james-d">James D.
                            Hodgson</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Japan Desk Officer - William Piez</item>
                    <item>Defense Department</item>
                    <item>Secretary of Defense - <persName corresp="#p_schlesinger-james-r">James R.
                            Schlesinger</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Assistant Secretary of Defense (<gloss target="#t_isa">ISA</gloss>) -
                            <persName corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Robert Ellsworth</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Assistant for Japan (<gloss target="#t_isa">ISA</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_eapr">EAPR</gloss>) - LTC W.R. Barrett, <gloss
                            target="#t_usaf">USAF</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>Time: 1520-1530, 27 June 1974<lb/>Place: Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_schlesinger-james-r">Schlesinger</persName>’s Office,
                    Pentagon</p>
                <p>I. (<gloss target="#t_u">U</gloss>) General Discussion</p>
                <p>After opening courtesies, Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_hodgson-james-d"
                        >Hodgson</persName> indicated that he and Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Ellsworth</persName> had covered several
                    issues concerning Japan earlier (see below), and asked if Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_schlesinger-james-r">Schlesinger</persName> had any further
                    items to discuss. <gloss target="#t_secdef">SecDef</gloss> commented that our
                    relations with Japan were cordial at present, but that there were relatively
                    minor on-going issues such as homeporting and funding of U.S. consolidation in
                    Japan. Due to other commitments, the meeting was brief, and was concluded with
                    Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_hodgson-james-d">Hodgson</persName> inviting
                    Mr. <persName corresp="#p_schlesinger-james-r">Schlesinger</persName> to visit
                    Japan at the earliest opportunity.</p>
                <p>2. (C) Discussion between Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_hodgson-james-d"
                        >Hodgson</persName> and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert"
                        >Ellsworth</persName>
                </p>
                <p>Prior to meeting <gloss target="#t_secdef">SecDef</gloss>, Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_hodgson-james-d">Hodgson</persName> and Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Ellsworth</persName> discussed several current
                    Japan issues. Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Ellsworth</persName>
                    made the Ambassador aware of major <gloss target="#t_goj">GOJ</gloss>
                    construction efforts on Okinawa and in the Tokyo area concerning the
                    consolidation of U.S. forces, and of the potential for slippage in the
                    construction timetable. As U.S. forces budget reductions are geared to the
                    timetable, pressure should be maintained on the <gloss target="#t_goj"
                        >GOJ</gloss> to adhere to the schedule. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Ellsworth</persName> also discussed the impact
                    of Japan’s current <pb facs="d191-2" n="2" xml:id="d191-2"/> economic slowdown
                    on the Japanese military program, and the U.S. interest in having the Japanese
                    continue with gradual improvement of her military forces. Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Ellsworth</persName> then reiterated the U.S.
                    interest in having Japan ratify the <gloss target="#t_npt">NPT</gloss>, and
                    concluded the discussion with the comment that recent problems relative to
                    visits to Japan of U.S. nuclear-powered warships had been resolved, although the
                    subject may surface again.</p>
                <p>Memorandum of Conversation<lb/>Prepared by: LTC Barrett</p>
                <p>Approved by: [signed] <persName corresp="#p_ellsworth-robert">Robert
                        Ellsworth</persName>
                    <lb/> Date: 5 July 74</p>
                <p>Distribution: <lb/>
                    <gloss target="#t_secdef">SecDef</gloss> (1)<lb/>DepSecDef (1) <lb/>
                    <gloss target="#t_osd">OSD</gloss> (CCS) (1)<lb/>ASD (<gloss target="#t_isa"
                        >ISA</gloss>) (1)<lb/>State Dept (<gloss target="#t_ea">EA</gloss>/J)
                    (1)<lb/>Mil Asst/SecCef (1)<lb/>R&amp;C (2)<lb/>AD (1)</p>
            </div>
